Component	Purpose
ESP32	Main microcontroller
BioAmp EXG Pill	Bio-signal amplifier
Gel Electrodes	Signal acquisition from skin
Robotic Hand + Servos	Actuation
Jumper Wires	Connections
External Power Source	Power supply
🔌 Hardware Connections
EXG Pill → ESP32

OUT → ESP32 Analog Pin (GPIO34 or GPIO35)
VCC → 3.3V
GND → GND

Electrodes Placement

Three electrodes are used:
Signal electrode → muscle group (forearm or target muscle)
Reference electrode → nearby muscle area
Ground electrode → bony area (elbow or wrist)

This configuration helps reduce noise and improve signal quality.
